<div id="review_2496340387" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2496340387" />
    <a title="Curt Cannon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41125421-curt-cannon"><img alt="Curt Cannon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546574305p2/41125421.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2496340387?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Curt Cannon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Curt Cannon" href="/user/show/41125421-curt-cannon">Curt Cannon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2496340387" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4596574584497400589">Lincoln’s life is inspiring, and Sandburg is both exhaustive in his research and almost poetic with his prose. The first third of the book is particularly good, as is the last couple of chapters describing the assassination and the national mourning that followed. The one downside is that it is a little bit choppy in its flow, being an abridged version of Sandburg’s original 6-volume edition. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

