<span id="freeTextContainer127587770467485620">Carl August Sandburg was an American writer and editor, best known for his poetry. He won two Pulitzer Prizes, one for his poetry and another for a biography of Abraham Lincoln. H. L. Mencken called Carl Sandburg &quot;indubitably an American in every pulse-beat&quot;.<br/><br/>For more info see <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Sandburg'>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_San...</a></span>
  <span id="freeText127587770467485620" style="display:none">Carl August Sandburg was an American writer and editor, best known for his poetry. He won two Pulitzer Prizes, one for his poetry and another for a biography of Abraham Lincoln. H. L. Mencken called Carl Sandburg "indubitably an American in every pulse-beat".<br /><br />For more info see <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Sandburg">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_San...</a></span>
